  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.10.2-stable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nCan send ETH\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThe transaction stays in the queue and cannot be broadcast.\r\nThere are several such transactions every day.\r\n\r\n#### I use the official docker image to start it\r\n```\r\ndocker run --name=eth --net coin-network -v /home/core/data/eth/ethereum:/root/.ethereum ethereum/client-go:v1.10.2 --snapshot=false --syncmode fast --http --http.api=eth,net,web3 --http.addr 0.0.0.0 --http.vhosts *\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nMy program uses HTTP_RPC's sendRawTransaction to send transactions, and occasionally the transaction stays in the queue and cannot be broadcast. \r\nI am sure that my node is working well, and I have given sufficient gas_limit and gas_price. \r\nFor example, this transaction: [0xfbb16033af0181f320fe3e786d0718e1107aab860a42c6a4436fcc13f335c5f7](https://etherscan.io/tx/0xfbb16033af0181f320fe3e786d0718e1107aab860a42c6a4436fcc13f335c5f7) \r\nWhen it stops on my node (using geth attach --exec txpool.content I can see its existence), I use nodes of other platforms, and it can broadcast successfully and quickly.\r\n\r\nI have also tried to use a third-party node https://infura.io/ to broadcast transactions for my program, but it also has the above situation, so I suspect that it is not only my node that has this problem.\r\n\r\nThis situation has become more and more frequent recently, and it bothers me a lot. Who can provide me with some help?\r\n",
